
1) Enter 3 numbers from the user & make a function to print their average.

ANS:-


import java.util.*;
public class Main
{
      public static void printAvarage(int a,int b, int c){
        int avarage= (a+b+c)/3;
       System.out.println(avarage);
        
    }    
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	    Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
	    System.out.println("enter 3 number");
	    int a= sc.nextInt();
	    int b= sc.nextInt();
	    int c= sc.nextInt();
	     System.out.println("the avarage are::");
	     printAvarage(a,b,c);
	}
}


2) Write a function which takes in 2 numbers and returns the greater of those two

ANS:-

import java.util.*;
public class Main
{
    
    public static void printGreater(int a,int b){
        if(a>b){
            System.out.println(a);
        }
        else{
            System.out.println(b);
        }   
    }    
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	    Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
	    System.out.println("enter 2 numbers::");
	    int a= sc.nextInt();
	    int b=sc.nextInt();
	    System.out.println("greater is:");
	    printGreater(a,b);
	}
}


3)
